  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Does reishi mushroom actually help with sleep?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Multiple studies suggest reishi improves sleep quality without acting as a sedative. A 2012 study in the Journal of Ethnopharmacology found that 3 days of reishi extract (80mg/kg) significantly increased total sleep time and non-REM sleep in animal models. A 2005 human study showed that patients with neurasthenia reported significantly improved sleep quality after 8 weeks of reishi supplementation. The mechanism involves GABAergic modulation and HPA axis regulation rather than direct sedation, meaning reishi helps normalize sleep patterns rather than forcing drowsiness.' },
